73.7	Irenaeus	Irenaeus	Irenaeus (Greek: ), (2nd century AD â€“ c. 202) was Bishop of Lugdunum in Gaul, then a part of the Roman Empire (now Lyons, France). He was an early church father and apologist, and his writings were formative in the early development of Christian theology. He was a hearer of Polycarp, who in turn was a disciple of John the Evangelist.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/13/Saint_Irenaeus.jpg/200px-Saint_Irenaeus.jpg
